    "encrypted": "false",
    "instructions_important": "false",
    "long_instructions": "#### Musical Conversation\r\n\r\n**Define:** You're creating a song inspired by musical conversations, where one sound makes a statement and another replies. This technique, called *call and response*, is used in jazz, hip-hop, and Afro-Caribbean music to create rhythm and dialogue.\r\n\r\n**Prepare:** Pick two different sound packs to pull from (ie: Groove or Pop or Electro). Plan how one will act as the \"call\" and the other as the \"response.\" Consider how you can use different combinations of beat, bass, and lead tracks from each pack.\r\n\r\n**Try:** Create at least 3 sections where one sound makes a musical \"call\" and another responds. Use sequencing and rests to alternate between them. Each section should sound unique and easy to tell which pack it came from.\r\n\r\n**Reflect:** Does your remix feel like a conversation? In order to complete this level, your remix must include:\r\n\r\n- At least 3 unique beat tracks\r\n- At least 3 unique bass tracks\r\n- At least 3 unique lead tracks\r\n- A musical dialogue created by offsetting and varying tracks",
